Anne Hampson ( b. November 28 in England ) was a popular British writer of over 125 romance novels in Mills & Boon from 1969 to 1998 . She also has published as Jane Wilby historical romance novels . Although she retired in 1998 , in 2005 she published two romance and a crime novels . She has published her autobiography . Anne Hampson dreamed to teach and to write when was six , but due to the depression after World War II , she had to let study at 14 . She had to begin to make blouses Marks & Spencer 's blouses . She let work when marrying . Later , when her marriage broke up , she had to return to work and to live in a tiny caravan . But , when Manchester University decided to trial older women she applied and she graduated . 